      <p class="lead">
        The distance between a compelling vision and tangible reality is filled with failed dreams, abandoned projects, and unrealized potential. The difference between those who achieve their visions and those who don't isn't talent or luck—it's mastery of execution.
      </p>

      <h2 id="execution-gap">The Great Execution Gap</h2>

      <p>
        Research across industries reveals a consistent pattern: organizations and individuals excel at creating strategies and setting goals but struggle dramatically with implementation. Studies suggest that 70% of strategic initiatives fail due to poor execution, not poor strategy.
      </p>

      <p>
        This execution gap exists because we fundamentally misunderstand what execution requires. We treat it as the simple act of "doing the work," when in reality, execution is a sophisticated skill requiring strategic thinking, psychological awareness, systems design, and adaptive problem-solving.
      </p>

